Elsa!

*A kingdom of greenhouse gases
Only Bill Nye seems to care*
yaha
*It's time I show the strength of an evil queen*
Nooo..
*I built a hoard of evil snowmen*
Oh, no!
*They're gonna take over the world*
*I hope you concentrate in camp (Heil Elsa)*
What?! *Let my troops march on*
Oh my gosh..
Nazi?
Oh my God!
Are they comparing Elsa to Hitler?
*The cold's coming back and it's here to stay..*
*I sunk like a brick*
*Prince thinks I'm sick*
*Ice is melting quick*
*Now I have a lot of self esteem ..*
I get it!
Beautiful!
Damn beautiful.
That is awesome... oh my God! I love that guy!
I'm glad Katrina was a while ago, because I would be really f**ked up.
I just love these, can he make a 3rd one? And have it just come out tomorrow already?
What did you think of this song?
That was really creative I liked it
I don't know how he comes up with that!
It's genius!
I think it was probably an extremly great song but i just didn't get it.
Because i haven't seen a lot of these movies, I wasn't into princess movies
I watched the first one actually like i got to it because of Teens React so.. and i subsribed him because of Teens React
So you reacted to the first one he did another episode
Yeah long time ago..
It was very good sequel
I was in the other one with like little mermaid and Belle, "bestiality"..
I normally never choose sequels but I really like the 2nd one!
Because it's like kind of dark humor that i like..
So break down each of these moments, first was Mulan. The song about her maybe wanting to actually become a man after dressing like a man.
Was it your thought on that take on the Mulan story?
I honestly, I think that's hilarious!
I don't think that that's what Disney was trying to say..
It's not wrong...
I feel like he's trying to like say something, like he has like little, of little politic in gender.
The question is, what happened to Shane? The love interest from mulan, did he end up becoming a girl or did they have a gay marriage together?
Then the cinderella who ended up in an insane asylum
Yeah that's sad
'Ey, you know what before i met you my carriage was a pumkin.'
If she ever told anyone about that they'd be like "You're f*cking crazy!"
Then princess Tiana, whos resteraunt's washed away in hurricane Katrina and automatically dies.
That's so sad!
But when you put on that perspective, that's hilarious!
This guy, I mean he knows what he's doing, Disney should hire him.
That's like a truth, that's like a real truth to what happened to the princess and a frog!
Then finally Elsa from Frozen, turning a snowmen army into the basically nazi version of Frozen.
What do you think of that as a plot for Frozen 2?
That's just like not okay.
That would be terrible!
She's like Hitler!
I gues so our Jewish community wouldn't be too good with that.
I don't think Elsa was enough of an Evil Queen she was too victimised, so I think it's hilarious that..
..she actually turns into an Evil Queen and takes over the world to preserve it.
Some people have made comments on this video saying that he went too far. Why is that okay or not okay to this type of thing in your opinion?
I think it's perfectly fine.
I thought that was fantastic!
That's what I call a humor!
..like any joke except of that jokes you can offend anyone.
Comparing it to like such a bad things like hurricane Katrina when so many people died and then like The Holocaust, I feel like that's pretty bad.
We have to laugh at this things because it shows that like we moved on, we got through it.
Comedy does not have any borders.
We can say all or we can say nothing. You can't pick and choose about who says what.
So let's talk about John who made this video, what do you think of his abilities?
I think that's really cool. He made a quartet with himself.
This video like as a whole was really, really clever.
From a musical aspect it's really difficult to do, to layer all the voices get the timing correct
That's like a lot of work! And how does he.. because obviously he does it all individual videos.
So how does he like staying time with himself when he's not singing with himself.. Teach me!
So both After Ever After have milions of views, why is this concept so virial?
I don't know! It's just.. it's different princesses.. so I guess people want to see what happens to the other princesses..
He's really funyy, I mean just the idea behind the kids movies.
So many people into Disney, anyone can like listen to that and know what he's talking about.
He's a good looking guy, he's a really.. obviously really talented! And he's doing it all acapella
There is so many different aspects of it that are interesting so someone from like an editing point of view is like a 'Oh you know that's really cool,  I could do something like that!'
People have their owns concepts or theories what happens after and then he's making jokes about what happenes after, fantastic!
So with these videos he's making a point that 'happily ever after' may not excist. Do you believe in living 'happily ever after'?
No, not really, I mean i think you can get real close
Life isn't like that!
I'm only going to be happy for the majority of my life.
No, because it's always something that happens that makes you not so happy.
Happiness is something that comes from inside of you, so I mean it's up to you whether you wanna live happily ever after or not.
I want a 'happy ever after' for me. So that's why i watch this movies and i'm like "Good, good for that happy ever after, now where is mine?
Yes, when i'll get married and i'll have like 5 kids then i'll just like live happy ever after.
With who?
With who? Harry Styles... Duhhh.
